description: Follow live text commentary, score updates and match stats from AFC Wimbledon vs Harrogate Town in the League Two
title: AFC Wimbledon vs Harrogate Town: League Two stats & head-to-head
title_page: AFC Wimbledon vs Harrogate Town: League Two stats & head-to-head - BBC Sport
maintext:
AFC Wimbledon are unbeaten across their five league games against Harrogate Town in the EFL (W3 D2), winning the reverse fixture 3-0 in December.
Harrogate Town have won just two of their 19 Football League games against sides from London (D5 L12), though both victories have come on the road – 2-0 vs Leyton Orient in August 2021 & 2-1 vs Sutton United in January 2024.
AFC Wimbledon have lost two of their last four home league games (W1 D1), as many defeats as across their prior 19 outings at Plough Lane beforehand combined (W13 D4).
Harrogate have failed to win any of their last seven away league games (D2 L5), failing to score in each of their last five. That’s already the longest run that the Yorkshire side have endured on the road in the EFL without scoring.
